Sentence: Someone left their umbrella in the hallway.
Someone : indefinite pronoun, singular, subject of the verb "left"
left : verb "leave", past tense, third person singular
their : possessive determiner, singular they, modifying "umbrella"
umbrella : common noun, singular, direct object of the verb "left"
in : preposition indicating location
the : definite article, modifying "hallway"
hallway : common noun, singular, object of the preposition "in"

Sentence: Did anyone see the missing keys on the counter?
Did : auxiliary verb, past tense, used to form a question
anyone : indefinite pronoun, singular, subject of the verb "see"
see : main verb, base form following auxiliary "did"
the : definite article, modifying "keys"
missing : adjective, modifying "keys"
keys : common noun, plural, direct object of the verb "see"
on : preposition indicating location
the : definite article, modifying "counter"
counter : common noun, singular, object of the preposition "on"

Sentence: Everyone enjoyed the surprise party at Sarah's house.
Everyone : indefinite pronoun, singular, subject of the verb "enjoyed"
enjoyed : verb "enjoy", past tense, third person singular
the : definite article, modifying "party"
surprise : noun acting as an adjective, modifying "party"
party : common noun, singular, direct object of the verb "enjoyed"
at : preposition indicating location
Sarah's : proper noun, possessive case, modifying "house"
house : common noun, singular, object of the preposition "at"

Sentence: Nobody knows the answer to that difficult question.
Nobody : indefinite pronoun, singular, subject of the verb "knows"
knows : verb "know", present tense, third person singular
the : definite article, modifying "answer"
answer : common noun, singular, direct object of the verb "knows"
to : preposition connecting "answer" and "question"
that : demonstrative determiner, modifying "question"
difficult : adjective, modifying "question"
question : common noun, singular, object of the preposition "to"

Sentence: Something strange is happening in the old laboratory.
Something : indefinite pronoun, singular, subject of the verb "is happening"
strange : adjective, post-positive modifier for "something"
is : auxiliary verb, present tense, third person singular
happening : main verb "happen", present participle forming continuous aspect
in : preposition indicating location
the : definite article, modifying "laboratory"
old : adjective, modifying "laboratory"
laboratory : common noun, singular, object of the preposition "in"

Sentence: Each student must submit their assignment by Friday.
Each : indefinite determiner, singular, modifying "student"
student : common noun, singular, subject of the verb "must submit"
must : modal auxiliary verb indicating obligation
submit : main verb, base form following modal "must"
their : possessive determiner, singular they, modifying "assignment"
assignment : common noun, singular, direct object of the verb "submit"
by : preposition indicating deadline
Friday : proper noun, singular, object of the preposition "by"

Sentence: Every cloud has a silver lining eventually.
Every : indefinite determiner, singular, modifying "cloud"
cloud : common noun, singular, subject of the verb "has"
has : verb "have", present tense, third person singular
a : indefinite article, modifying "lining"
silver : adjective, modifying "lining"
lining : common noun, singular, direct object of the verb "has"
eventually : adverb, modifying the entire clause or verb "has"

Sentence: Both candidates offered excellent solutions during the debate.
Both : indefinite determiner, plural, modifying "candidates"
candidates : common noun, plural, subject of the verb "offered"
offered : verb "offer", past tense, plural agreement
excellent : adjective, modifying "solutions"
solutions : common noun, plural, direct object of the verb "offered"
during : preposition indicating time
the : definite article, modifying "debate"
debate : common noun, singular, object of the preposition "during"

Sentence: You can choose either the red shirt or the blue one.
You : personal pronoun, second person, subject of the verb "can choose"
can : modal auxiliary verb indicating ability or permission
choose : main verb, base form following modal "can"
either : indefinite determiner, introducing the first of two options
the : definite article, modifying "shirt"
red : adjective, modifying "shirt"
shirt : common noun, singular, first object of choice
or : coordinating conjunction connecting two alternatives
the : definite article, modifying "one"
blue : adjective, modifying "one"
one : pronoun, substituting for "shirt"

Sentence: Neither option seems viable given the current budget constraints.
Neither : indefinite determiner, singular, modifying "option"
option : common noun, singular, subject of the verb "seems"
seems : verb "seem", present tense, third person singular
viable : adjective, subject complement describing "option"
given : preposition meaning "considering"
the : definite article, modifying "constraints"
current : adjective, modifying "constraints"
budget : noun acting as an adjective, modifying "constraints"
constraints : common noun, plural, object of the preposition "given"

Sentence: Someone called while you were out running errands.
Someone : indefinite pronoun, singular, subject of the verb "called"
called : verb "call", past tense, third person singular
while : subordinating conjunction indicating time
you : personal pronoun, second person, subject of the verb "were running"
were : auxiliary verb, past tense, plural or second person
out : adverb indicating absence from home
running : main verb "run", present participle forming continuous aspect
errands : common noun, plural, direct object of the verb "running"

Sentence: Is there anything else we need to buy for the trip?
Is : auxiliary verb, present tense, third person singular, inverted for question
there : existential dummy subject
anything : indefinite pronoun, singular, real subject of the sentence
else : adverb, modifying "anything"
we : personal pronoun, first person plural, subject of the verb "need"
need : verb "need", present tense, plural agreement
to : particle introducing the infinitive verb
buy : main verb, infinitive form
for : preposition indicating purpose
the : definite article, modifying "trip"
trip : common noun, singular, object of the preposition "for"

Sentence: Everyone in the office agrees that the project is behind schedule.
Everyone : indefinite pronoun, singular, subject of the verb "agrees"
in : preposition indicating location
the : definite article, modifying "office"
office : common noun, singular, object of the preposition "in"
agrees : verb "agree", present tense, third person singular
that : subordinating conjunction introducing a noun clause
the : definite article, modifying "project"
project : common noun, singular, subject of the verb "is"
is : linking verb, present tense, third person singular
behind : preposition indicating status or location
schedule : common noun, singular, object of the preposition "behind"

Sentence: Nobody told me about the meeting change until noon.
Nobody : indefinite pronoun, singular, subject of the verb "told"
told : verb "tell", past tense, third person singular
me : personal pronoun, first person singular, indirect object of "told"
about : preposition indicating topic
the : definite article, modifying "change"
meeting : noun acting as an adjective, modifying "change"
change : common noun, singular, object of the preposition "about"
until : preposition indicating time
noon : common noun, singular, object of the preposition "until"

Sentence: Something delicious smells like it is cooking in the kitchen.
Something : indefinite pronoun, singular, subject of the verb "smells"
delicious : adjective, post-positive modifier for "something"
smells : verb "smell", present tense, third person singular, linking verb
like : conjunction introducing a clause of comparison
it : personal pronoun, third person singular, subject of "is cooking"
is : auxiliary verb, present tense, third person singular
cooking : main verb "cook", present participle forming continuous aspect
in : preposition indicating location
the : definite article, modifying "kitchen"
kitchen : common noun, singular, object of the preposition "in"
